The paper deals with error correction in binary polymer strings used for data storage, which involves techniques from information theory (cs.IT) and coding theory (cs.DS). The use of composition multisets and polynomial factorization also suggests connections to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational complexity (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes a Reed-Solomon type coding redundancy, which is a common technique in coding theory (cs.CC).
